From mlachwani@gmail.com Mon May 06 00:00:00 2026
From: Manish Keshav Lachwani <mlachwani@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 06 May 2026 00:04:00 +0530
Subject: [RFC PATCH 4b/4] mm/Kconfig: add CONFIG_KV_MADVISE option
Message-ID: <20260506-kv-cpu-madvise-rfc-v1-4b@gmail.com>
In-Reply-To: <20260506-kv-cpu-madvise-rfc-v1-0@gmail.com>
References: <20260506-kv-cpu-madvise-rfc-v1-0@gmail.com>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8

Add a Kconfig option so the Linux MM side of the KV madvise extension
can be compiled out entirely on kernels that do not want or need
device-dispatch behavior for MADV_KV_*.

This keeps the RFC easier to evaluate experimentally while making the
feature explicitly opt-in, matching reviewer expectations for new
behavior in mm/.

Signed-off-by: Manish Keshav Lachwani <mlachwani@gmail.com>
---
 mm/Kconfig | 13 +++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+)

diff --git a/mm/Kconfig b/mm/Kconfig
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/mm/Kconfig
+++ b/mm/Kconfig
@@ -1043,6 +1043,19 @@ config USERFAULTFD
 	  more details and examples.
 
+config KV_MADVISE
+	bool "KV-cache madvise device dispatch hooks"
+	depends on MMU
+	help
+	  Enable experimental MADV_KV_HOT, MADV_KV_EVICT, and
+	  MADV_KV_PREFETCH dispatch hooks in the memory-management
+	  subsystem.
+
+	  These hooks allow userspace runtimes to issue semantic
+	  KV-cache hints through madvise(2), which are translated
+	  into device-specific callbacks by a registered near-memory
+	  compute driver.
+
+	  If unsure, say N.
+
 endmenu
 
 config HAVE_ARCH_USERFAULTFD_WP
